        dwc:phylum         "Arthropoda" ;
        dwc:rank           "genus" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4612391>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Fig. 39. Characteristics of sperm and spermiogenesis of Stenoonops peckorum. A: The chromatin condenses irregularly in developing spermatids and appears fibrillar. B: A single-layered manchette of microtubules surrounds the nucleus. C: The IF is very small and contains only the two centrioles. D: During further development, the nucleus extremely elongates. E: The short peN is thin and flag shaped. F: The AF, which originates from the subacrosomal space, clearly ends before the base of the axoneme. G: At the end of spermiogenesis, the main sperm cell components coil." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4612391/files/figure.png" .

