<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4612385>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Fig. 37. Characteristics of synspermia of Silhouettella loricatula. A: Numerous sperm conjugates, as well as electron-dense secretions, are visible in the lumen of the deferent ducts. B: Section through sperm conjugates indicates the organization of sperm that are arranged in the center of synspermia, surrounded by heterogeneous cytoplasm. C: The nuclei show a peculiar chromatin-condensation pattern. D: The periphery of the sperm conjugate is composed of small membrane stacks. The entire sperm conjugate is surrounded by a thin secretion sheath." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4612385/files/figure.png" .

